history.content:
You do not need to take EECS 47D if you have taken math 54. If you plan to take EECS 47D, you need to get the permission code from a professor. You need to do homework once professors start to teach circuits. You need to take the second midterm and final.

---------------------

Just to clarify on other user's student answer - as someone who is in 47D right now, you do have to take it to fulfill the requirement for EE16A if you are in EECS. However, if you are L&S CS, you can just take Math 54 and EE16B if you think you can get away with self studying circuits.

You do not need to take EECS 47D if you have taken math 54. If you plan to take EECS 47D, you need to get the permission code from a professor. You need to do homework once professors start to teach circuits. You need to take the second midterm and final.
